			<h3>Budapest University of Technology and Economics</h3>
			<div class="clearfix">
				<p class="left">Budapest University of Technology and Economics (BUTE) was founded in 1782 and since then, it considers its role as to develop international relation, improve knowledge and international reputation of professors, researchers and students. The university develops co-operations <strong>promoting research and education</strong> in the field of international relations and evolves different forms of mobility.
				</p>
				<p class="left">Major targets of the university are to broaden the international education programs and to participate in mobility programs supported by the European Union. As one of the biggest Hungarian universities, BUTE <strong>focuses on the quality and on the high standard of teaching</strong>, hence it is considered one of the best engineering school.</p>
			</div>
			<p class="full">The University reputation has been growing. (approx. 5000 international students have graduated here), since the 80's regular full time programs in English have been offered in BSc, MSc. and PhD. levels.  3000 international students have joined the University programs in mobility schemes for one or two semesters.
